Associate Director of Pricing - Quik Dubai, United Arab Emirates Apply Careem is building the Everything App for the greater Middle East — making it easy to move around, order food and groceries, manage payments, and more. Our purpose is simple: to simplify and improve people’s lives and build an awesome organisation that inspires. Since 2012, Careem has enabled earnings for over 2.5 million Captains, simplified the lives of more than 70 million customers, and built a platform where the region’s best talent and entrepreneurs thrive. We operate in 70+ cities across 10 countries, from Morocco to Pakistan. 
 We’re now entering our next chapter — one powered by AI. We’re looking for AI talent: curious problem-solvers who know how to apply AI to build tools, automate workflows, and create real impact. Whether it’s streamlining operations, enhancing customer experience, or reimagining internal systems — we want people who can make Careem work smarter and move faster. About the Role As the  Associate Director of Pricing , you will own the strategic roadmap for how we price essential grocery items across our diverse markets. This isn't just about managing a spreadsheet; it’s about treating pricing as a  strategic lever  to drive growth, customer loyalty, and sustainable margins. You will have the autonomy to build a best-in-class pricing engine from the ground up for one of the region's fastest-growing grocery platforms. You’ll be at the intersection of commercial strategy and cutting-edge product development. You will lead the transition from manual pricing to a sophisticated, productized, and automated ecosystem. We are looking for a data-driven leader who can balance the "art" of competitive retail with the "science" of algorithmic automation. 
 What you'll do 

 Strategic Vision:  Design and execute the long-term pricing strategy for Careem Quik across multiple markets, ensuring alignment with regional consumer behaviors and business goals. 
 Product & Tech Partnership:  Collaborate deeply with Product and Engineering teams to build "productized pricing"—moving away from manual inputs toward automated, scalable systems. 
 Experimental Frameworks:  Design and lead rigorous pricing experiments to quantify  price elasticity  and consumer sensitivity, using these insights to refine our value proposition. 
 Commercial Optimization:  Partner with the Commercial and Category teams to strike the perfect balance between  market competitiveness  and  bottom-line margins . 
 Execution Oversight:  Ensure that the central strategy is localized and implemented accurately across all operating territories. 
 Performance Analytics:  Monitor daily pricing health, identifying opportunities for margin expansion without sacrificing our "best-in-market" promise for essential goods. 

 What you'll need 

 Experience:  Minimum  8+ years  in Pricing, Revenue Management, or Strategy, specifically within  Grocery (Offline or E-commerce) , FMCG, or High-Frequency Retail. 
 Data Mastery:  Expert-level proficiency in data analytics (SQL, Python, or R preferred). You should be comfortable navigating large datasets to extract actionable elasticity models. 
 Automation Mindset:  Proven track record of working with tech teams to automate pricing workflows and implement dynamic pricing logic. 
 Strategic Thinker:  You see pricing as a tool for market share and customer lifetime value, not just a tactical cost-plus calculation. 
 Communication:  Ability to translate complex analytical findings into clear strategic recommendations for C-suite stakeholders. 
 Adaptability:  Experience managing pricing across multiple geographical markets with varying competitive landscapes. 

 What we’ll provide you 
 We offer colleagues the opportunity to drive impact in the region while they learn and grow. As a full time Careem colleague, you will be able to: 

 Work and learn from great minds by joining a community of inspiring colleagues. 
 Put your passion to work in a purposeful organisation dedicated to creating impact in a region with a lot of untapped potential. 
 Explore new opportunities to learn and grow every day. 
 Work 4 days a week in office & 1 day from home, and remotely from any country in the world for 30 days a year with unlimited vacation days per year. (If you are in an individual contributor role in tech, you will have 2 office days a week and 3 to work from home.) 
