_apply":false,"display_departments":true,"display_search_bar":true,"display_new_jobs_tag":true,"display_number_of_open_jobs":true,"display_footer":true,"candidate_portal_enabled":true,"application_tracking_enabled":false,"seek_id":"","enable_recruitics":true,"appcast_tracking_code":null,"google_drive_enabled":true,"enable_dropbox":true,"allow_external_notifications":true,"display_job_trust_profiles":false,"grayscale_ai_bot_enabled":false,"grayscale_ai_bot_access_token":null},"urlToken":"careem","embedded":false,"isJobPost":true},"routes/$url_token_.jobs_.$job_post_id":{"jobPost":{"post_type":"job_post","language":"en","title":"Commercial Coordinator - Food","hiring_plan_id":6352578002,"content":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAbout the Role\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWe are seeking a detail-oriented and proactive Commercial Coordinator to join our Account Management Team. This is a full-time role based in Karachi, supporting the UAE based Account management team in the Food Vertical. This role will be pivotal in supporting our commercial operations, ensuring smooth execution of partner relationships, and enabling growth across multiple portfolio accounts. The successful candidate will act as the backbone of the team, providing coordination, reporting, and cross-functional support to drive efficiency and excellence in delivery.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat you'll do\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAccount \u0026amp; Partner Support\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAssist the Account Managers in day-to-day partner management.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCoordinate onboarding and operational processes for new enterprise partners.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eSupport in maintaining up-to-date partner records, contracts, and commercial terms.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eEnsuring partners are equipped with login credentials and internally raising requests for tablet changes/new tablet requests, ads requests and configurations, sending onboarding documents to the catalog teams to ensure outlets are live on time without default.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eEnsuring campaign activation and deactivation on time.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCommercial Operations\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eTrack, monitor, and report on deals, campaigns, and performance KPIs.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCoordinate and raise promotional campaigns and initiatives, ensuring their participation.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eEnsuring the correct discounts/value are being portrayed on the app and flagging/ rectifying accordingly.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eEnsure timely follow-up on action items and deliverables with stakeholders.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eEscalate technical or operational LIVE issues to relevant teams for resolution and following up with them for resolution.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCross-Functional Coordination\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eLiaise with internal teams (Operations, Marketing, Finance, Legal, and Product) to support Account Management initiatives.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAct as the first point of contact for resolving operational or administrative issues.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCoordinate partner-related campaigns, ensuring alignment across teams and on-time execution.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eProcess \u0026amp; Efficiency\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAssist in streamlining commercial workflows and implementing best practices.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eIdentify opportunities for improving documentation, reporting, and partner communication.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eEnsure compliance with internal policies and procedures.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat you'll need\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eBachelor’s degree in Business, Economics, or a related field.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e1–3 years of experience in commercial coordination, account management support, or operations (preferably in tech, FMCG, or e-commerce).\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eStrong organizational and multitasking abilities with attention to detail.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eProficiency in MS Office/Google Workspace (Excel/Sheets, PowerPoint/Slides).\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eExcellent communication and interpersonal skills.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAnalytical mindset with the ability to interpret data and generate insights.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eA proactive, solution-oriented attitude with the ability to work in a fast-paced environment.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat we’ll provide you\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWe offer colleagues the opportunity to drive impact in the region while they learn and grow. As a full time Careem colleague, you will be able to:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eWork and learn from great minds by joining a community of inspiring colleagues.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003ePut your passion to work in a purposeful organisation dedicated to creating impact in a region with a lot of untapped potential.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eExplore new opportunities to learn and grow every day.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eWork 4 days a week in office \u0026amp; 1 day from home, and remotely from any country in the world for 30 days a year with unlimited vacation days per year. (If you are in an individual contributor role in tech, you will have 2 office days a week and 3 to work from home.)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAccess to healthcare benefits and fitness reimbursements for health activities including gym, health club, and training classes.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e","introduction":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"\u003eCareem is building the Everything App for the greater Middle East — making it easy to move around, order food and groceries, manage payments, and more. Our purpose is simple: to simplify and improve people’s lives and build an awesome organisation that inspires.\u003c/span\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"\u003eSince 2012, Careem has enabled earnings for over 2.5 million Captains, simplified the lives of more than 70 million customers, and built a platform where the region’s best talent and entrepreneurs thrive. We operate in 70+ cities across 10 countries, from Morocco to Pakistan.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"\u003e\u003cstrong data-stringify-type=\"bold\"\u003e\u003cem data-stringify-type=\"italic\"\u003eWe’re now entering our next chapter — one powered by AI. We’re looking for AI talent: curious problem-solvers who know how to apply AI to build tools, automate workflows, and create real impact. Whether it’s streamlining operations, enhancing customer experience, or reimagining internal systems — we want people who can make Careem work smarter and move faster.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","conclusion":"","enable_eeoc":false,"job_post_location":"Karachi, Pakistan","public_url":"https://boards.greenhouse.io/careem/jobs/8397725002?gh_jid=8397725002","company_name":"Careem","confirmation_message":"\u003cp\u003eWe are thrilled that you are interested to be part of Careem!\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWe have received your application and one of our Recruiters will review it. Due to the volume of applications, we are unable to give a response to all applications, and prioritize the ones th